quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,55,"And indeed, they are enraging us,"
  26,56,"And indeed, we are a cautious society..."
  26,57,"So We removed them from gardens and springs"
  27,28,"Take this letter of mine and deliver it to them. Then leave them and see what [answer] they will return."
  27,29,"She said, "
  27,30,"Indeed, it is from Solomon, and indeed, it is [i.e., reads]: 'In the name of Allāh, the Entirely Merciful, the Especially Merciful,"
  28,1,"Ṭā, Seen, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  28,2,"These are verses of the clear Book."
  28,3,"We recite to you from the news of Moses and Pharaoh in truth for a people who believe."